In the Matter of KENMORE GRANVILLE HOTEL CO., Debtor. Nettie MEYER et al. v. SECURITIES SERVICE CORPORATION. No. 5704. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Feb. 27, 1936. Meyer Abrams, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Claude A. Roth, Harry E. Smoot, Max Frederick Goldberg, Irving Flamm, Arthur M. Cox, and Isaac E. Ferguson, all of Chicago, Ill., for appellees.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and AL-SCHULER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellees, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the ‘same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
